The combined effect of the intermediate Fröhlich coupling and soft lattice can be probed by measuring the sub-band gap absorption, which is characterised by the Urbach energy (see Supplementary Note 6)46. We determined the temperature-dependent Urbach energy (depicted in Fig. 3a) from optical transmittance measurements (see Supplementary Note 2). For the principal interacting phonon mode, we obtained an energy of 18.8 meV (in excellent agreement with the 19 meV A1g mode), and an estimated steepness parameter of σ0̂=0.58\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
